<subSubSection box="[151,524,1876,1902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,524,1876,1902]" box="[151,524,1876,1902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="368">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,524,1876,1902]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,524,1876,1902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="368">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Pallas, 1766" authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1766" box="[238,524,1876,1902]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Antipathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,368,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="368">Antipathes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pallas" box="[375,524,1876,1902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" refString="Pallas, P. S. (1766) Elenchus zoophytorum sistens generum adumbrationes generaliores et specierum cognitarum succinctas descriptiones cum selectis auctorum synonymis. Hagae-Comitum, Frankfurt am Main, 500 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 6595" type="book" year="1766">Pallas, 1766</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="369" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1946,2007]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,392]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="369" pageId="1" pageNumber="368">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1766" box="[151,271,1946,1971]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Antipathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,271,1946,1971]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="368">Antipathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the oldest black coral genus, and is distinguished by colonies that are branched, with branching patterns varying from fan-shaped to bushy (
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko" box="[694,1019,1982,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" refString="Opresko, D. M. &amp; Sanchez, J. A. (2005) Caribbean shallow-water black corals (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Antipatharia). Caribbean Journal of Science, 41, 492 - 507." type="journal article" year="2005">Opresko &amp; Sanchez, 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko" box="[1040,1218,1982,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" refString="Opresko, D. M. (1972) Redescriptions and reevaluations of the antipatharians described by L. F. de Pourtales. Bulletin of Marine Science, 22, 950 - 1017." type="journal article" year="1972">Opresko, 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Like the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1834" box="[151,299,151,176]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Antipathidae</taxonomicName>
, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1766" box="[424,544,151,176]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Antipathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[424,544,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Antipathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered a taxonomic dumping ground that includes highly heterogeneous forms (
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko" box="[230,582,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" refString="Opresko, D. M. &amp; Baron-Szabo, R. C. (2001) Re-descriptions of the antipatharian corals described by E. J. C. Esper with selected English translations of the original German text (Cnidaria, Anthozoa, Antipatharia). Seckenbergiana biologica, 81, 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="2001">Opresko &amp; Baron-Szabo, 2001</bibRefCitation>
). Even though many species have been removed from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1766" box="[1189,1309,188,213]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Antipathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1189,1309,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Antipathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and placed into new genera (
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko" box="[362,538,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" refString="Opresko, D. M. (2006) Revision of the Antipatharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa). Part V. Establishment of a new family, Stylopathidae. Zoologische Mededelingen Leiden, 80 - 4, 109 - 138." type="book chapter" year="2006">Opresko, 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko" box="[554,613,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" refString="Opresko, D. M. (2004) Revision of the Antipatharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa). Part IV. Establishment of a new family, Aphanipathidae. Zoologische Mededelingen Leiden, 78, 209 - 240." type="journal article" year="2004">2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko" box="[630,689,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" refString="Opresko, D. M. (2003) Revision of the Antipatharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa). Part III. Cladopathidae. Zoologische Mededelingen Leiden, 77, 495 - 536." type="journal article" year="2003">2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko" box="[706,765,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" refString="Opresko, D. M. (2002) Revision of the Antipatharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa). Part II. Schizopathidae. Zoologische Mededelingen Leiden, 76, 411 - 442." type="journal article" year="2002">2002</bibRefCitation>
, 2001; 
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko" box="[859,1154,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" refString="Opresko, D. M. &amp; Cairns, S. D. (1994) Description of the new genus Allopathes (Cnidaria: Antipatharia) and its type species Cirripathes desbonni. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 107, 185 - 192." type="journal article" year="1994">Opresko &amp; Cairns, 1994</bibRefCitation>
), the genus still groups numerous species that are morphologically and phylogenetically heterogeneous, and is therefore in need of further revisions (
<bibRefCitation author="Brugler" box="[269,499,295,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" refString="Brugler, M. R., Opresko, D. M. &amp; France, S. C. (2013) The evolutionary history of the order Antipatharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) as inferred from mitochondrial and nuclear DNA: implications for black coral taxonomy and systematics. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 169, 312 - 361. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12060" type="journal article" year="2013">
Brugler 
<emphasis box="[365,424,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">et al.</emphasis>
, 2013
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bo" box="[513,621,296,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" refString="Bo, M. (2008) Taxonomy and ecology of antipatharians. Universita Politecnica Delle Marche, Ancona, 212 pp." type="book" year="2008">Bo, 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<collectingCountry box="[635,712,296,319]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">France</collectingCountry>
<emphasis box="[721,780,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">et al.</emphasis>
, 2007). Two species have previously been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,254,332,357]" name="Bermuda" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Bermuda</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1857" box="[269,400,332,357]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Antipathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[269,400,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">A. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1857" box="[454,565,332,356]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Antipathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis box="[454,565,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">A. furcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Locke" box="[579,778,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" refString="Locke, J. M., Coates, K. A. &amp; Bilewich, J. P. (2013) Scleractinia, Octocorallia and Antipatharia of Bermuda's reefs and deepwater coral communities: a taxonomic perspective including new records. In: Sheppard, C. R. C. (Ed.), Coral Reefs of the United Kingdom Overseas Territories, Coral Reefs of the World. Vol. 4. Springer, Dordrecht, pp. 189 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 007 - 5965 - 7 _ 14" type="book" year="2013">
Locke 
<emphasis box="[656,712,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
), both of which were recorded as part of this survey (
<tableCitation captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,440,463]" captionText="TABLE 1. Black coral specimens examined as part of this study (BAMZ = Bermuda Aquarium, Museum and Zoo; NR = not reported; * = new record for Bermuda)." pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
